There exists a difference between Dominica and the Dominican Republic. The Republic is a part of the island of Hispaniola, the latter is a separate island. Thus, it would be incorrect to call "Dominica" the "la République dominicaine," as that title would go to the Dominican Republic. [[User:Lord Emsworth|Lord Emsworth]] 10:35, 21 Oct 2003 (UTC)

